<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-219-067 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 506 952</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Feb 19 1991 v5 n7 p21(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Macweek 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ardis network links to SprintNet. (joint venture between Motorolaand IBM)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   ARDIS (Products)International Business Machines Corp. (Joint ventures).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     ConnectivityNetworksInternetworkingJoint Venture.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Lincolnshire, Ill.andP;  -- What could be more convenient than a wireless network?andO;According to Ardis Co., the answer is a wireless network that connects to anestablished public data network.andM;Ardis, a joint venture between IBM Corp. and Motorola Inc. that provideswireless data network services, announced that it has joined with US SprintCommunications Inc. to connect to hosts on the SprintNet nationwide network.andM;With the new connection, Ardis users in the field will be able to communicatewith each other and with non-wireless mainframes, minis, and microcomputersvia a gateway between Ardis and SprintNet.andM;Like most public data-access networks, SprintNet supports a wide variety ofprotocols, connections and services that permit connection to a range ofcomputers.andP;  Ardis provides the gateway between its wireless WAN andSprintNet.andP;  Users pay separately for SprintNet access and services, such aselectronic mail.andM;Ardis Co. is at 300 Knightsbridge Parkway, Lincolnshire, Ill.andP;  60069.andP;  Phone(708) 913-1215; fax (708) 913-1453.andO;</TEXT></DOC>